# UI & Styling

Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first `@theme`) + shadcn/ui. Tokens live in
`packages/ui/src/styles/theme.css`; rationale in `docs/design-system.md`.

## Rules

- **Use semantic utilities**, not hard-coded colours: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`,
  `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `bg-accent`, `border-border`, `ring-ring`.
  Primitive scales (`bg-brand-500`, `text-sun-600`, `neutral-*`) are for rare brand moments.
- **Never** write hex values or arbitrary colours (`text-[#...]`) in components.
- Shared, reusable components live in `@odyssey/ui`. Compose them in apps; don't fork them.
- Follow shadcn/ui patterns: `cva` for variants, `cn()` from `@odyssey/ui/lib/utils` to merge
  classes, `asChild` via Radix `Slot` for polymorphism.
- Dark mode is class-based (`.dark`); rely on semantic tokens so it "just works".
- Multi-market theming overrides **semantic** tokens only (`--primary`, `--background`, ...),
  never the primitive scales.
- **Accessibility is mandatory** (see `accessibility.mdc`): AA contrast for every token
  pairing, visible focus states, and full keyboard operability on all interactive UI.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="bg-[#2892a7] text-white" />

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground" />
```
